    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved gradation 2 vs. required 3) is accepted based on regulatory precedent for standard-compliant ASTM F1717 submissions and the low incremental risk associated with a single standard test configuration. All three QoIs satisfy both quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is assessed as adequately credible for the stated COU. Note: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; digital signature is pending completion of the institutional signature workflow and has not been applied to this submission.",
